MyBroadband’s speed test platform gives South African broadband users the ability to test their Internet connection speed, and rate their Internet service provider (ISP). [Test your speed here] These consumer ratings are used to compile monthly and quarterly reports, which rank South African fibre, DSL, and wireless ISPs based on speed and customer satisfaction. To ensure a neutral testing environment, MyBroadband’s HTML5 speed test servers are hosted in Teraco’s vendor-neutral data centres. Through NAPAfrica, all network operators present at its peering points are provided with a free 10Gbps connection to MyBroadband’s speed test platform. MyBroadband is giving away prizes worth R5,000, including an Amazon Kindle, a Google Chromecast, and branded gear, to encourage you to do a speed test. To stand a chance to win one of these great prizes, here is what you should do: The giveaway will run until 22 October 2018, and the winners will be announced shortly afterwards.